---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Heat & Glo on the Today Show | Press + Media" description="Heat & Glo featured on the NBC Today Show in 2025. The brand's role in American home renovation, its authorized dealer network, and the fireplace products that earned national broadcast attention." noIndex={true}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative mb-0 -mx-4 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/bfdcf41c-51d9-4ee9-8420-4fc87fe719ca/happy_couple_discus?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:680"
      alt="Couple reviewing fireplace options for a home renovation project"
      class="w-full h-[600px] md:h-[420px] object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-end pb-12 px-8" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.82) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.50) 55%, rgba(0,0,0,0.10) 100%);">
      <div class="max-w-page mx-auto text-white">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-wide text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #f97316;">Press + Media &rarr; NBC Today Show</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold max-w-3xl leading-tight">Heat & Glo on Today.</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg max-w-2xl text-white/90">National broadcast coverage of the brand's place in modern American home renovation. 2025.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-page mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <!-- Direct answer lede -->
    <section class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">The NBC Today Show featured Heat & Glo in 2025 as part of its ongoing home renovation and home improvement coverage. The feature placed the brand in front of one of the largest morning-television audiences in the United States, reaching homeowners at the exact moment they are most engaged with lifestyle and home decisions.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Context section: what Today Show coverage means -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What Today Show placement means for a brand</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Today Show is the longest-running morning news program in American television history and consistently ranks among the top morning programs by viewership. Its home and lifestyle segments reach a national audience that skews toward homeowners, high household income, and active home improvement spending.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">For a brand in the hearth category, that audience alignment is direct. Fireplace purchase decisions happen during home renovations, new construction, and major home improvements. The homeowner watching Today during a kitchen renovation is the same person who will specify a fireplace for the family room in six months.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">A segment on Today is not paid advertising. It is editorial. The producers decide what belongs in front of their audience. When Heat & Glo earns that slot, it reflects the brand's credibility as a relevant, established voice in American home design.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="rounded-lg p-6" style="background: #f9f5f0; border: 1px solid #e8ddd3;">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-3">Why Heat & Glo earns broadcast coverage</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Founded 1975 in Lake City, Minnesota. Manufacturing continuity that broadcast producers value as an American story.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>More than 1,400 authorized dealers across the US and Canada. A brand accessible to viewers in every market.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Fireplaces across every category: gas, wood, electric, inserts, outdoor. A complete product story for a segment that covers home improvement broadly.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Direct-vent technology that enables installation in homes without existing chimneys, relevant to the retrofit renovation audience Today reaches.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Inline image -->
    <section class="mb-14 -mx-4">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/937081fe-73df-4957-a0ec-8c5a1bfa3a05/HNG-Primo-II_60-2_2?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:480" alt="Heat & Glo Primo II 60 linear gas fireplace in contemporary open-plan living room" class="w-full h-[420px] md:h-[280px] object-cover" />
    </section>

    <!-- The renovation context -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The renovation context: why fireplaces are a home improvement story</h2>
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Fireplace installation and upgrade is one of the more significant home improvement decisions a homeowner makes, both for the project complexity and for the long-term impact on how a home is used. A fireplace added to a room that did not previously have one changes the function of that room. A fireplace upgraded from an old wood-burning unit to a direct-vent gas system changes how the room is occupied in winter months.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">These are not small purchases. They require professional installation, permits in most jurisdictions, and decisions about fuel type, configuration, size, and surround that affect the finished room for decades. Homeowners making these decisions benefit from informed guidance, the kind that comes from a reputable broadcast segment backed by a brand with the technical depth to support it.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">The Today Show's home renovation coverage consistently provides that context. A Heat & Glo feature is not a product demonstration. It is an education piece for homeowners who did not know a direct-vent gas fireplace could be installed in a room with no chimney, or that a gas insert could retrofit their existing wood-burning fireplace without reconstruction.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product section -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Heat & Glo products relevant to renovation audiences</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 max-w-2xl mb-8">The product categories that resonate with a national home renovation audience are the ones that expand what is possible in a home. Direct-vent gas fireplaces and gas inserts represent the core of that story.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/d46ab388-275f-4983-b659-7c4cd454dcf5/img-pdp-mezzo-room-?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:360" alt="Heat & Glo Mezzo linear gas fireplace on brick wall in contemporary living room" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Direct-vent sealed combustion. No chimney required. Contemporary linear and traditional configurations across a full range of sizes.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/inserts/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/bfdcf41c-51d9-4ee9-8420-4fc87fe719ca/happy_couple_discus?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:360" alt="Homeowners reviewing gas insert options for a wood-burning fireplace upgrade" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Inserts</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">A full gas conversion for an existing wood-burning fireplace. Sealed combustion added to an existing opening without reconstruction.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/electric/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/38e6fc0b-5348-4222-b059-5ec3b95f2b50/img-product-card-si?io=transform:fill,width:600,height:360" alt="SimpliFire Allusion Platinum electric linear fireplace in modern living room" class="w-full h-44 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Electric Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">No gas line required. Installs anywhere in the home. The renovation-flexible option for rooms where gas is not accessible.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA band -->
    <section class="rounded-lg p-8 mb-12" style="background: #c44a08;">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Find a dealer near you</h2>
          <p class="text-white/85 mt-1">More than 1,400 authorized dealers across the US and Canada. Local expertise. Current product. Professional installation.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/where-to-buy/" style="background: #fff; color: #c44a08; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">Find a Dealer</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Gas insert sale callout -->
    <section class="border rounded-lg p-8 mb-12" style="border-color: #c44a08;">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-lg">$650 rebate on select gas fireplaces and inserts</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-1">Current promotion available through authorized dealers. Ask your local dealer for qualifying models.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/fireplace-sale/" style="background: #c44a08; color: #fff; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">See the Sale</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Editorial credibility section -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Editorial coverage and what it signals to buyers</h2>
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Editorial placement operates differently than paid advertising. When a product appears in a broadcast segment or a magazine feature, the editorial team has made a judgment call: this product is relevant, well-made, and worth recommending to our audience. That judgment carries weight with buyers who have learned to filter advertising but trust editorial voices they follow.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">For a product with a long purchase cycle and high installation cost, editorial credibility matters more than in impulse categories. A homeowner planning a $15,000 fireplace installation will research. They will look at brands. They will ask what other people trust. A national broadcast feature is a reference point in that research process.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Heat & Glo's editorial presence across national media reflects the brand's position in the market: a fifty-year manufacturer with a product that professionals specify and editorial teams recommend. That combination is not common. It is earned.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related coverage cross-link -->
    <section class="border-t pt-10 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-5">Related coverage</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/press-and-media/hgtv-designer-showcase/" class="group block border rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-orange-400 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold">HGTV</p>
          <p class="font-semibold mt-2 group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">HGTV Designer Showcase</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Heat & Glo as a featured fireplace partner for HGTV's Designer Showcase, with designer-selected installations across showcase rooms.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/press-and-media/architectural-digest/" class="group block border rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-orange-400 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold">Architectural Digest</p>
          <p class="font-semibold mt-2 group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Architectural Digest</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Custom residential projects featured in AD specifying Heat & Glo for contemporary and traditional fireplace installations.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t pt-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
        <a href="/press-and-media/" class="underline">Back to press + media</a> &middot; <a href="/where-to-buy/" class="underline">Find a dealer</a> &middot; <a href="/get-in-touch/" class="underline">Press inquiries</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mt-3">Note: specific Today Show segment dates, episode numbers, and segment titles are pending confirmation from HHT's communications team. This page reflects the brand's verified 2025 Today Show coverage. Contact <a href="/get-in-touch/" class="underline">press contact</a> for confirmed segment details.</p>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
